headline: After Disappointing in 2025, These Blue-Chip Dividend Stocks Are Way Too Cheap
summary: These five top blue-chip stocks underperformed last year and look poised to rebound in 2026. Two are Warren Buffett holdings in Berkshire Hathaway.

headline: Walmart’s $611 Billion Annual Revenue: Breaking Down $1.7 Billion Per Day
summary: Walmart (NYSE:WMT) generated $681 billion in revenue during fiscal 2025, translating to $1.87 billion per day. But here’s the metric that matters more than that staggering topline number: Walmart’s operating margin. headline: Target Expands Beauty Assortment As Store Experience And Leadership Evolve
summary: Target (NYSE:TGT) is launching its largest Spring beauty assortment, adding more than 3,000 mostly budget-friendly products across stores. The retailer is rolling out refreshed in-store beauty layouts, interactive displays, and exclusive events to reshape the shopping experience. Target is also making further leadership changes, including new board members with experience at Nike, Walmart, and HanesBrands.
